The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	 Mohun Bagan rode Amitava Chakrabortys 104 to a eight-wicket win over Belgachia United in the CAB senior division league on Sunday.       
	SUMMARISED SCORES      
	 Belgachia United Club 228. Mohun Bagan 229/2 (A. Chakraborty 104). MB won by 8 wkts.       
	 East Bengal 391/6. Kumartuli Institute 166 (P. Mukherjee 6/43). EB won by 225 runs.       
	 Kalighat 297/9. Shambazar Club 310/8 (S.S. Mondal 70). Shambazar won by 2 wkts.       
	 Mohammedan Sporting 360/9. Dalhousie Athletic Club 353/9 (N. Srivastav 75). Match drawn.          
	 Calcutta Port Trust (CPT) thrashed Police AC 5-2 in their Beighton Cup preliminary league match at the SAI complex on Sunday.           
	 DPS, Ruby Park and Birla High School led the junior and senior sections, respectively, after the fifth round in the Inter-School Chess Championship organised by the Dibyendu Barua Chess academy at the Childrens Book Fair, Salt Lake on Sunday.                
	Hockey: Beighton Cup at SAI complex from 2pm.      
	Chess: Inter-School meet at Childrens Book Fair from 1pm.                                                                                                                                                                     
